## Cross-cutting requirements (every preset)

### Accessibility (WCAG 2.2 AA minimum)

✅ Color contrast ratio ≥4.5 normal text / ≥3 large text
✅ Focus visible states (2px outline lub equivalent)
✅ Touch targets ≥24×24px mobile
✅ Color NIE jest sole indicator (use icons + text)

### Performance

✅ Fonts subset + preload (woff2 only, max 2 font families)
✅ Images max 250kb hero / max 50kb thumbnails
✅ CSS critical inline (above fold), rest async
✅ JS lazy by default

### Polish-market readiness

✅ Polish characters (ą/ć/ę/ł/ń/ó/ś/ź/ż) render OK w fontach
✅ Polish patterns (NIP/REGON display, +48 phone, postal code XX-XXX)
✅ RODO compliance w cookie banner
✅ WCAG dla podmiotów publicznych

### Brand override capability

✅ Klient w admin SiteSettings może override (single CSS variable swap):
- Primary color
- Display font (Google Fonts dropdown)
- Brand voice tone

## Anti-patterns

❌ **Hardcoded fonts/colors w samples** — wszystko via CSS variables (override-friendly).

❌ **Hardcoded English w samples** — Polish first.

❌ **React-specific patterns** (np. `useState`, JSX z hooks) — generated HTML target = framework-agnostic (Astro consumer).

❌ **Heavy animations bez prefers-reduced-motion check** — accessibility violation.

❌ **Brak full-page.html sample** — preview verification wymagane.

## Validation per preset

Każdy preset MUSI pass:
- Lighthouse Performance ≥90 dla full-page.html (mocked content)
- Lighthouse Accessibility ≥95
- Lighthouse SEO ≥95
- Color contrast WCAG AA all combinations
- Polish character render (visual test z "Łódź żółw pięć")
- Schema validation tokens.example.json

